hi!! We're a little late to the party but we're finally holding our GBM for the semester!

Whether you're a new member or you've been with us before, you're all invited to join us as we talk about what we have planned for the rest of this semester! @everyone As someone that has benefited directly and greatly from the sponsorships and programs run by ***Break Through Tech Chicago***, and their services that are UIC-first, I wanted to request you all to help us get them a bigger spotlight (which eventually helps in getting better funded, and better equipped with resources, etc).  
 
Here's a message directly from them:  
> I am asking your support to vote for Break Through Tech Chicago at UIC by October 17 to win the People’s Choice Award at the annual Chicago Innovation Awards! In a few easy steps, you can celebrate our progress of doubling the enrollment of UIC women and nonbinary students in tech disciplines since 2019.
> Visit https://bit.ly/3llmP1X and click the SEE THE TOP 100 FINALISTS AND CAST YOUR VOTE button.
> Fill in your name and email address, and press the button at the bottom of the page to move on to the voting process. *Yes you have to go through every page before you can submit. 
> 
> We are listed on the first page of finalists. Select our name and scroll through all remaining names till you get to “Submit”.
> Thank you for using your vote to voice the importance of gender equity in Chicago’s tech scene.
 
Your time commitment: <2min. Commitment to equity in tech? Long-lasting!
Thank you for giving us your time! 
- Yashi, President

content: @everyone CyberForce 2023 is a national competition. The team will get a small network of virtual machines mimicking a company that is wide open with no security controls.
